headline: The WSJ Dollar Index Rises 0.10% to 100.46
summary: Yields and the WSJ Dollar Index were above yesterday levels before the 10 a.m. data and fell afterward.  The 10-year yield is at 4.196% and the WSJ Dollar Index falls less than 0.1%.  The prospect of the Federal Reserve cutting interest rates faster than the market expects and uncertainty over fiscal policy implementation under U.S. President-elect  Donald Trump  could lead to a temporary dollar fall at the start of 2025.

headline: Billionaire Stanley Druckenmiller Sold 95% of Duquesne's Stake in Palantir and Is Piling Into This High-Yield Dividend Stock Instead
summary: Druckenmiller nearly exited his fund's position in one of Wall Street's hottest artificial intelligence (AI) stocks to buy a sizable stake in a boring company with exceptional pricing power.

headline: China Services Activity Gauge Signals Continued Growth, Optimism
summary: A private gauge of China’s services activity suggests that the sector has continued to expand, with firms’ optimism at a seven-month high as Beijing’s policy support boosted market confidence.
